On April 30, 1986, the Edmonton Oilers lost the Stanley Cup. The next season they set out to win it back again. And you can be there. On the ice. In the dressing room. And on the road with THE BOYS ON THE BUS.

This revealing behind-the-scenes account of one of the youngest and most successful teams of our time. Through candid interviews with the &quot;great ones,&quot; Gretzky, Messier, Fuhr, Coffey, Lowe, and Sather, you'll have the rare opportunity to experience firsthand, the camaraderie, loyalty, and physical &amp; mental commitment required of professional athletes.

This film takes you from the Oilers' heart-breaking defeat by the Calgary Flames in 1986, to their triumphant 1987 resurrection as Stanley Cup champions and the best hockey team in the world.

